    "raw_text": "Grants\nWe’re excited to announce the launch of our new Grant Page on our website! This page is designed as a valuable resource for businesses, organizations, and non-profits in our district to gain insight on the grant process.\nHere, you can find up-to-date information on open grant applications, gain assistance when applying for grants, and view our interactive map to see which grants have been awarded throughout the 9th District. Our goal is to provide you with an interactive and informative resource that can assist in your quest for funding.\nIf you ever need help navigating the grant process or have questions about our Grant Page, please do not hesitate to reach out to our office. We’re here to assist you in any way we can!\nClick here\nto read about all of the grants that been awarded in the 9th District!\nDownload Grant & Resource Directory\nCurrent Funding Opportunities\nSection 319 Nonpoint Source Management\nAgency: PA Department of Environmental Protection\nDeadline: Applications open 04/22/24, deadline TBA\nLearn More & Apply\nJudicial Outreach Liaison Program (JOL)\nAgency: PA Department of Transportation\nDeadline: 5/31/2028\nLearn More & Apply\nGrowing Greener\nAgency: PA Department of Environmental Protection\nDeadline: Applications open 04/22/24, deadline TBA\nLearn More & Apply\nStatewide DUI Program Coordination\nAgency: PA Department of Transportation\nDeadline: 5/31/2029\nLearn More & Apply\nAct 101, Section 902 Recycling Program Development and Implementation\nAgency: PA Department of Environmental Protection\nDeadline: 5/10/2024\nLearn More & Apply\nStatewide Traffic Records Program Support\nAgency: PA Department of Transportation\nDeadline: 5/31/2030\nLearn More & Apply\nMunicipal Fire Department Capital Grants\nAgency: PA Office of the State Fire Commissioner\nDeadline: 5/15/2024\nLearn More & Apply\nStatewide Law Enforcement Liaison Program Coordination (PTS)\nAgency: PA Department of Transportation\nDeadline: 5/31/2031\nLearn More & Apply\nEmergency Training Center Capital Grants\nAgency: PA Office of the State Fire Commissioner\nDeadline: 5/15/2024\nLearn More & Apply\nChild Passenger Safety Educational Initiatives\nAgency: PA Department of Transportation\nDeadline: 5/31/2032\nLearn More & Apply\nAbandoned Mine Drainage Abatement and Treatment Program\nAgency: PA Department of Community & Economic Development\nDeadline: 5/31/2024\nLearn More & Apply\nDistracted Driving Outreach\nAgency: PA Department of Transportation\nDeadline: 5/31/2033\nLearn More & Apply\nFlood Mitigation Program\nAgency: PA Department of Community & Economic Development\nDeadline: 5/31/2024\nLearn More & Apply\nAct 101, Section 901 County Planning and Hazardous Household Waste Education\nAgency: PA Department of Environmental Protection\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nPublic School Facility Improvement\nAgency: PA Department of Community & Economic Development\nDeadline: 5/31/2024\nLearn More & Apply\nAIE Residencies\nAgency: PA Council on the Arts\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nCommunity Traffic Safety Project\nAgency: PA Department of Transportation\nDeadline: 5/31/2024\nLearn More & Apply\nCreative Catalyst Grants\nAgency: PA Council on the Arts\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nAutomated Red Light Enforcement Transportation Enhancements Grant Program (ARLE)\nAgency: PA Department of Transportation\nDeadline: 06/30/24\nLearn More & Apply\nCreative Entrepreneur Accelerator Program\nAgency: PA Council on the Arts\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nCapital Improvement Matching Grants\nAgency: PA Department of Agriculture\nDeadline: 6/30/2024\nLearn More & Apply\nLocal Law Enforcement Grant Program\nAgency: PA Gaming Control Board\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nAgricultural Fair Operating and Premium Reimbursement Program\nAgency: PA Department of Agriculture\nDeadline: 11/15/2024\nLearn More & Apply\nCertified Local Government Mini-Grants\nAgency: PA Historical and Museum Commission\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nMunicipal Police Traffic Services Enforcement Program\nAgency: PA Department of Transportation\nDeadline: 5/31/2025\nLearn More & Apply\nAct 190, Chapter 2 Household Hazardous Waste Collection Grant\nAgency: PA Department of Environmental Protection\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nSewage Facilities Program\nAgency: PA Department of Community & Economic Development\nDeadline: 5/31/2025\nLearn More & Apply\nHost Municipality Review of Permit Applications Grants\nAgency: PA Department of Environmental Protection\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nState Agricultural Organization Funds Reimbursement\nAgency: PA Department of Agriculture\nDeadline: 11/15/2025\nLearn More & Apply\nHost Municipality Siting Review Grants\nAgency: PA Department of Environmental Protection\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nDUI Courts Program\nAgency: PA Department of Transportation\nDeadline: 5/31/2026\nLearn More & Apply\nPennsylvania’s Long Term Care Grant\nAgency: PA Department of Health\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nWatershed Restoration and Protection Program\nAgency: PA Department of Community & Economic Development\nDeadline: 5/31/2026\nLearn More & Apply\nFoundations in Industry Training Grant Program\nAgency: PA Department of Community & Economic Development\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nCounty FFA Funds Reimbursement\nAgency: PA Department of Agriculture\nDeadline: 11/15/2026\nLearn More & Apply\nMunicipal Assistance Program\nAgency: PA Department of Community & Economic Development\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nTraffic Safety Resource Prosecutor\nAgency: PA Department of Transportation\nDeadline: 5/31/2027\nLearn More & Apply\nPeer and Circuit Rider Grants\nAgency: PA Department of Conservation and Natural Resources\nDeadline: No deadline\nLearn More & Apply\nCounty 4-H Funds Reimbursement\nAgency: PA Department of Agriculture\nDeadline: 11/15/2027\nLearn More & Apply\nGrants Awarded in the 9th District\nSenate Democratic Policy Committee Hearing on Lowering Your Electric Bill\nHARRISBURG, PA − June 23, 2026 − Senate Democratic Policy Committee Chair Nick Miller (D-14) hosted a policy hearing examining solutions to lower consumer electric bills, alongside Senator Kane and Senator Malone. Experts provided testimony regarding strategies to...\nread more\nTartaglione, Kane, Robinson Accessibility Bill Signed into Law as Act 16 of 2026\nHarrisburg, PA, May 6, 2026 – Today, Senators Tina Tartaglione (D-2, Philadelphia), John Kane (D-9, Chester/Delaware), and Devlin Robinson (R-37, Allegheny) announced that Senate Bill 867 has been signed into law by the Governor, becoming Act No. 16 of 2026. The...\nread more\nSenator John I. Kane and Senate Democrats Urge Penn State to Respect Graduate Workers and Bargain in Good Faith\nHARRISBURG, PA – April 21, 2026 − State Senator John I. Kane (D–Delaware/Chester) announced that he has joined his Senate Democratic colleagues in calling on Penn State University leadership to respect the will of its graduate assistants and move forward with good...\nread more\nPA Senate Democrats Write Letter of support for Penn State-UAW\nApril 13, 2026: The Pennsylvania Senate Democrats sent the following letter of support for Penn State-UAW:\nread more\nState Senator John I. Kane and State Representative Carol Kazeem Announce Upcoming Free Senior Expo\nCHESTER, PA – March 31, 2026 – State Senator John I. Kane and State Representative Carol Kazeem are pleased to announce their upcoming Senior Expo on Thursday, April 9th, 2026. The event will be held at the Furey Road Fieldhouse, located at 8500 Furey Rd, Upper...\nread more\nSenator John Kane Announces Over $7.2 Million in Transportation and Infrastructure Grants for District 9\nHARRISBURG, PA — January 20, 2026 − Senator John Kane (D–Delaware/Chester) today announced more than $7.2 million in state grant funding awarded to communities across Senate District 9 through the Multimodal Transportation Fund and the PA Small Water and Sewer...\nread more\nSenator Kane Announces Over $6.1 Million in Local Share Account Funding for Infrastructure, Public Safety, and Community Projects Across the 9th Senatorial District\nHARRISBURG, PA — Senator John Kane (D–Chester/Delaware) today announced more than $6.1 million in Local Share Account (LSA) grant funding awarded to municipalities, counties, authorities, and nonprofit partners throughout the 9th Senatorial District, supporting...\nread more\nSenator John Kane Introduces Resolution Recognizing December 2 as World Nuclear Energy Day in Pennsylvania\nHARRISBURG, PA – December 2, 2025 − State Senator John Kane (D–Chester/Delaware), co-chair of the bipartisan and bicameral Nuclear Energy Caucus, announced today that he has introduced a resolution officially recognizing December 2, 2025, as World Nuclear Energy Day...\nread more\nSenator Kane Statement on Passage of the 2025–26 Pennsylvania Budget\nHarrisburg, PA − November 12, 2024 “After months of delay, I’m relieved that the 2025–26 Pennsylvania Budget has finally passed, and that it puts Pennsylvanians first. This budget is a responsible, balanced plan that delivers real results for working families,...\nread more\nSenator Kane Leads Pennsylvania Broadband Advocates in Urgent Letter to Gov. Shapiro to Protect $65M Digital Equity Funding\nOn June 30, 2025, Pennsylvania’s leading “broadband-for-all” advocates, including over 30 elected officials, sent a letter to Governor Shapiro urging him to challenge President Trump’s illegal termination of $65 million in federal “Digital Equity Act” grants. These...\nread more\nComitta, Kane Secure Funding for Good Fellowship Ambulance\nWest Chester, PA – July 7, 2025 – Good Fellowship Ambulance and EMS Training Institute, an emergency medical provider that covers ten municipalities in the West Chester area, is getting a new EMS-capable, all-terrain utility vehicles (UTV) thanks to grant funding...\nread more\nThe Pennsylvania Department of Health Announces Updates to Naloxone Standing Order\nThe Pennsylvania Department of Health has announced important updates to the state's Naloxone Standing Order, effective May 8, 2025. After thorough review and consultation with stakeholders including law enforcement and emergency services, Secretary of Health Dr....\nread more\nSenator Kane Announces Over $470,000 in Substance Abuse Prevention and Forensic Science Funding for Senate District 9\nJune 16, 2025 − Three local organizations have been awarded funding through the Pennsylvania Commission on Crime and Delinquency (PCCD) during their June 12 meeting. The awarded organizations include: PA State System of Higher Education Foundation: $174,428 for their...\nread more\nSenator Kane Announces Over $4 Million in Housing and Homelessness Prevention Funding for the 9th District\nHARRISBURG, PA − June 11, 2025 − State Senator John I. Kane today announced that the Pennsylvania Housing Finance Agency (PHFA) has approved funding for multiple projects in Chester and Delaware Counties through the Pennsylvania Housing Affordability and...\nread more\nSenate Labor and Industry Committee Unanimously Passes Legislation to Protect Construction Workers from Misclassification\nHARRISBURG, PA − June 10, 2025 − The Senate Labor and Industry Committee today unanimously passed Senate Bill 72, legislation that strengthens protections for construction workers who are misclassified as independent contractors. The bill, sponsored by Senators Kane,...\nread more\nSenate Democrats Hold Policy Hearing Regarding the Worker Protections\nPHILADELPHIA, PA − May 14, 2025 − Today, Senate Democratic Policy Committee Chair Nick Miller held a hearing to examine ways to protect Pennsylvania’s infrastructure and economy with a skilled, protected, and reliable workforce. “The testimony we heard today from...\nread more\nDelaware County Legislative Delegation Condemns Prospect F