    "title": "In the 9th",
    "url": "https://pasenatorkane.com/in-the-9th/",
    "date": null,
    "raw_text": "In the 9th\nCupcake Sisters\nIn this latest episode of “In the 9th” I visited the Cupcake Sisters, a wonderful women-owned and operated business right here in the 9th district in Glen Mills. It’s not just cupcakes they’re expertly crafting – they’ve expanded to designer cakes, cookies, and custom desserts, all baked from scratch daily!\nDuring my visit, I got the chance to chat with Tina and Nariman, the powerhouse sisters behind the operation, and even tried my hand at baking and decorating some cupcakes. Spoiler alert: it’s harder than it looks, but so much fun!\nI had an amazing time at our local bakery and I can’t wait to go back! It is such a treat to have local businesses like the Cupcake Sisters in the 9th at 364 Wilmington West Chester Pike, Glen Mills, PA. I encourage EVERYONE to drop by their bakery and try some of their mouthwatering treats! You won’t regret it!\nLearn more about Cupcake Sisters:\ncupcakesistersbakery.com\nFollow them on social media.\nFollow\nFollow\nLongwood Gardens\nJoin Senator Kane on an enchanting journey as he explores the magic of Longwood’s holiday retro-themed display in the latest episode of “In the 9th”. From the stunning display of over one million lights at Longwood to the dazzling tree decorations, join Senator Kane as he tours this gem of the 9th District!\nLearn more about Longwood Gardens:\nlongwoodgardens.org\nFollow them on social media.\nFollow\nFollow\nFollow\nFollow",
    "ai_summary": {
      "summary": "A Pennsylvania state senator visited two local businesses/attractions in his district — a bakery called Cupcake Sisters in Glen Mills and Longwood Gardens — filming promotional content for an ongoing video series called 'In the 9th.' The visits involved touring the locations and encouraging constituents to patronize them.",
      "action_type": "other",
      "topics": [
        "economy"
      ],
      "spin_flag": true
    }
  },
